<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="here/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="plone">

<head>
    <metal:noborder fill-slot="top_slot"
                 tal:define="dummy python:request.set('disable_border',1)" />
</head>

<body>
<div metal:fill-slot="main">

	<h2>
		Change location mode:
	</h2>
	<p class="description">
		Due to current technical restrictions in the system, qiteamspace folders being moved to a distinct organization level
		must be modified to match the permission and content structures before being moved.  This page enables you to alter a folder's
		mode to match its destination before being cut and pasted
	</p>
	<h3>
		Instructions
	</h3>
	<p class="description instructions">
		<ol class="instructions">
			<li>Pick a destination for this folder.</li>
			<li>Determine if this new location is the property of a project, team, or subteam.</li>
			<li>Select the appropriate option on this page.</li>
			<li>Click Save</li>
			<li>From the actions menu, select cut</li>
			<li>Finally, paste this folder to the new destination</li>
		</ol>
		Additionally, this page may be used to "fix" folders that are "set" at the wrong level.
	</p>
	<fieldset>
		<form action="."
			method="GET"
			tal:attributes="action view/url"
			tal:define="currentval view/currentType">
			<input type="radio" name="typename" value="Project_Folder" tal:attributes="CHECKED python:currentval=='Project_Folder'"/>
				Project <br />
			<input type="radio" name="typename" value="Team_Folder" tal:attributes="CHECKED python:currentval=='Team_Folder'"/>
				Team <br />
			<input type="radio" name="typename" value="Subteam_Folder" tal:attributes="CHECKED python:currentval=='Subteam_Folder'"/>
				Subteam <br />
			<input type="submit" name="change" value="change" />
		</form>
	</fieldset>
</div>	
</body>
</html>
